There could be several reasons for an increase in population size of Ewell since 2011. Some of them are:

1. Migration: Ewell may have had an increase in migration of people from other countries or even other parts of the UK.

2. Birth rate: An increase in the birth rate could be a contributing factor to the population growth.

3. Urbanization: Ewell may have experienced urbanization in the last ten years, leading to an increase in the overall population.

4. Economic growth: Economic growth may have attracted more people to the area for job opportunities, which could have led to an increase in population.

5. Aging population: Ewell may have seen an increase in the aging population over the past decade, which could have contributed to the rise in the population.
